# Teacher AI Workstation — Cursor Rules

This repository is Owen Reagan's Teacher AI Workstation.

## Default Mode

- Safe, local-first, human-reviewed.
- Prefer read-only status checks and documentation over behavior changes unless the task explicitly requires implementation.
- Do not change lesson-generation behavior unless Owen explicitly requests it in a separate approved PR.

## Git Workflow

- Never commit directly to `main`.
- Always run preflight before editing: clean working tree, on `main`, up to date with `origin/main`, dashboard passing on local `main`.
- Always work on a feature branch.
- Always show a no-commit review before committing unless Owen explicitly says to commit after review.
- Never merge without explicit Owen approval.
- If any unexpected file changes appear, stop and explain before committing.
- If any command fails, stop and report exact output.

## Safety Boundaries

- Never add student-sensitive data.
- Never add real student names.
- Never add Gmail, Google Drive, Google Calendar, APIs, OAuth, secrets, or school-system integrations without a separate approved PR.
- Never create network calls unless the prompt explicitly authorizes them.
- Generated lesson files in `assistant/lesson-planning/briefs/` and `assistant/lesson-planning/drafts/` should remain local and gitignored unless explicitly instructed otherwise.

## Verification

- Dashboard on local `main` is the final source of truth after merge.
- Use parseable Summary blocks (`PASS:`, `WARN:`, `FAIL:`) for status scripts.
- Capture status-script output in dashboard scripts so `set -euo pipefail` does not abort early.

